    skos:inScheme <https://metadatahub.eu/data/geologic-timescale> ;
    skos:definition "Global gap in the rock record between Precambrian basement and Cambrian strata; up to 1.2 billion years missing in places; cause debated: Snowball Earth glacial erosion, continental denudation, or Rodinia rifting; term coined by John Wesley Powell (1869); Lipalian interval of Walcott (1910)."@en ;
    gts:rank "Age" ;
