    skos:definition "Oldest stone tool traditions: Lomekwian (~3.3 Ma), Oldowan (~2.6 Ma, Homo habilis), Acheulean (~1.76 Ma, Homo erectus/heidelbergensis); hand axes; control of fire; covers c. 3.3 million to ~300,000 years ago. African archaeological periodization: ESA/MSA/LSA (distinct from European Paleolithic/Mesolithic/Neolithic framework)."@en ;
    gts:rank "CulturalAge" ;
    skos:broader ts:africa-prehistoric ;
    time:hasBeginning [ rdfs:label "3300000 BCE" ] ;
